cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CY 

This paper primarily focuses on the security and networking aspects of booter-based DDoS attacks, which are typically studied in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of the FBI takedown on the booter services, which falls under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper touches upon the financial and reputational damage caused by booter attacks, which is relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
